  "texts": [
    "The computing capabilities of edge devices have significantly improved in recent years, allowing for the processing Fig. 3 Emerging technologies related to IoT of complex algorithms and AI locally, leading to more efficient and intelligent agricultural systems (Lloret 2022).",
    "Drone Drones, also known as unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), have revolutionized agriculture by offering numerous benefits such as precision agriculture, cost savings, improved data collection, enhanced crop management, and increased safety for farmers (Nunes 2023).",
    "These UAVs play a crucial role in various agricultural tasks like plant health monitoring, weed control, spraying, and crop monitoring.",
    "The use of drones in agriculture contributes to sustainable farming practices by enabling precision spraying, irrigation, soil and field analysis, and bird control (Rathod and Shinde 2023).",
    "In agriculture, drones have manifold application areas as they can be integrated with novel technologies, computing capabilities, and onboard sensors to support crop management such as mapping, monitoring, irrigation, and plant diagnosis (Huang et al. 2021)."
  ]
}